definition.value: An undecenoic acid having its double bond in the 8-position.
A 16-hydroxy steroid that is prednisolone carrying a hydroxy group at the 16 position.

A hydroxamic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (4S,5R)-2-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-5-methyl-4,5-dihydro-1,3-oxazole-4-carboxylic acid with N-hydroxy-2-(1H-imidazol-4-yl)ethanamine. It is a biosynthetic intermediate in the synthesis of pseudomonine.
A member of the class of toluenes that is toluene substituted by a (1E)-12-carboxydodec-1-en-1-yl group at position 2.
This compound belongs to the class of organic compounds known as styrenes. These are organic compounds containing an ethenylbenzene moiety
A hydroxylamine that is  histamine in which the primary amino group is replaced by a hydroxyamino group.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-palmitoyl-L-alanine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A monomethylated phosphoethanolamine connected to a glucosylceramide having an iso-branched C17 long chain base and an undefined N-acyl chain composition.

A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (3'S)-2'-oxo-1',2',5,7-tetrahydrospiro[cyclopenta[b]pyridine-6,3'-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridine]-3-carboxylic acid with the amino group of (3S,5S,6R)-3-amino-6-methyl-1-(2,2,2-trifluoroethyl)-5-(2,3,6-trifluorophenyl)piperidin-2-one. It is a selective oral, small-molecule antagonist of calcitonin gene-related peptide (CGRP) receptor that has been approved for the treatment of migraine.
An antagonist at any calcitonin gene-related peptide receptor.
A glucosylceramide having an iso-branched C17 long chain base and an N-acyl chain with undefined composition.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-stearoyl-L-alanine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-oleoyl-L-alanine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-linoleoyl-L-alanine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-oleoyl-gamma-aminobutyric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-linoleoyl-gamma-aminobutyric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-palmitoyl-L-leucine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-stearoyl-L-leucine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A diterpenoid isolated from coffee silverskin. It inhibits cutaneous photoaging.
A diterpene glycoside that is atractyligenin having a single beta-D-glucuronic acid residue attached at position 2.
An undecenoate that is the conjugate base of 8-undecenoic acid.
A phosphorodiamide that is the active metabolite of the nitrogen mustard cyclophosphamide. It has potent antineoplastic and immunosuppressive properties.
